---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="About"
  description="Lynden Howells has over 35 years of full-time proofreading and editorial experience, working with government, universities, healthcare, and the private sector in Tasmania and across Australia."
>
  <div class="page-header">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>About Lynden</h1>
      <p class="page-header__sub">35+ years of full-time proofreading experience</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:auto 1fr;gap:3rem;align-items:start;">
        <div style="flex-shrink:0;">
          <img
            src="/lynden.jpeg"
            alt="Lynden Howells"
            width="180"
            style="border-radius:4px;border:3px solid var(--gold);display:block;"
          />
        </div>
        <div class="prose">
          <h2>Who I am</h2>
          <hr class="gold-rule" />
          <p>
            I am Lynden Howells, based in Hobart, Tasmania. For over 35 years I have worked
            full-time in the printing and publishing industry, with a focus on quality, accuracy,
            and speed of delivery. Whether you need a second pair of eyes on a short brochure or
            a thorough review of a complex annual report, I bring the same professional rigour to
            every job.
          </p>
          <p>
            I work with clients in person in Hobart and remotely — by phone, fax, and email —
            with clients across Tasmania and mainland Australia.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="prose mt-2">
        <h2>Career history</h2>
        <hr class="gold-rule" />

        <h3>2006 – Present &nbsp;<span class="text-gold">|</span>&nbsp; Freelance Proofreader &amp; Editor</h3>
        <p>
          Articles, journals, newsletters for colleges, government departments, scientific
          journals, and tender documents. Clients have included The Federal Group Tasmania,
          University of Tasmania, Clemenger Tasmania, Hobart College, and the Department of
          Health and Human Services.
        </p>

        <h3>2001–2005 &nbsp;<span class="text-gold">|</span>&nbsp; Curtis, Jones &amp; Brown, Balmain NSW</h3>
        <p>
          Healthcare advertising agency specialising in pharmaceutical detail aids and
          prescribing information — documents where precision is not optional.
        </p>

        <h3>1994–2001 &nbsp;<span class="text-gold">|</span>&nbsp; Clemenger Tasmania</h3>
        <p>
          Seven years at one of Tasmania's leading advertising agencies, covering the full
          range of client communications.
        </p>

        <h3>1988–1994 &nbsp;<span class="text-gold">|</span>&nbsp; Earlier roles</h3>
        <p>
          Penfold Buscombe, The Type Shop, Photolith, and the Printing Authority of Tasmania —
          foundational years in print production that built a deep understanding of how
          documents move from copy to press.
        </p>

        <h2>Types of work</h2>
        <hr class="gold-rule" />
        <ul>
          <li>Annual reports</li>
          <li>Scientific and academic journals</li>
          <li>Brochures and marketing collateral</li>
          <li>Tender documents</li>
          <li>Legal contracts</li>
          <li>Business cards, letterheads, and compliments slips</li>
          <li>Healthcare detail aids and prescribing information</li>
          <li>Newspaper advertisements</li>
          <li>Newsletters and government publications</li>
        </ul>

        <div class="highlight-box mt-2">
          <p style="margin:0;">
            "I guarantee to enhance anything you would like to produce in written form.
            Get in touch and let's discuss how I can help."
          </p>
          <p style="margin-top:0.75rem;font-weight:700;font-size:0.9rem;">— Lynden Howells</p>
        </div>

        <p class="mt-2"><a href="/contact" class="btn">Get in touch</a></p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  @media (max-width: 600px) {
    div[style*="grid-template-columns:auto 1fr"] {
      display: block !important;
    }
    div[style*="grid-template-columns:auto 1fr"] img {
      margin-bottom: 2rem;
    }
  }
</style>
